1
00:00:04,238 --> 00:00:06,173
(Minseok) ⟨I lost my Japanese parents when I was young →

2
00:00:06,240 --> 00:00:09,176
I was adopted by a Korean chaebol family→

3
00:00:09,243 --> 00:00:12,179
He was chased out of Korea after being accused of embezzlement.

4
00:00:12,246 --> 00:00:13,681
(Kyonhwa) Get out!

5
00:00:13,748 --> 00:00:17,685
(Minseok) ⟨In despair, I met Dr. Momoko, a doctor at the clinic...⟩

6
00:00:17,752 --> 00:00:20,187
(Momoko) There are words that I have always cherished.

7
00:00:20,254 --> 00:00:23,190
``There is no tree that will not fall even after being cut 10 times.''

8
00:00:23,257 --> 00:00:26,694
(Minseok) ⟨When I was young, I told you important words →

9
00:00:26,761 --> 00:00:28,696
I found out that it was that person⟩

10
00:00:28,763 --> 00:00:30,197
⟨but…⟩

11
00:00:30,264 --> 00:00:32,199
(Momoko) Takuto taught me this.

12
00:00:32,266 --> 00:00:34,702
(Minseok) ⟨Those words came from my childhood friend Takuto →

13
00:00:34,769 --> 00:00:36,704
I was supposed to teach you⟩

14
00:00:36,771 --> 00:00:39,206
(Takuto) Hey, could you please shut up?

15
00:00:39,273 --> 00:00:42,209
(Minseok) ⟨Meanwhile, I lost my place to live→

16
00:00:42,276 --> 00:00:45,713
I was allowed to live on the second floor of the Kazami clinic...⟩

17
00:00:45,780 --> 00:00:47,715
(Mizushima) You are such a hypocrite.

18
00:00:47,782 --> 00:00:50,217
(Momoko) Where was Minseok born and where did he grow up?

19
00:00:50,284 --> 00:00:52,219
It doesn't matter.

20
00:00:52,286 --> 00:00:54,221
(Minseok) ⟨ Even if you know about my background →

21
00:00:54,288 --> 00:00:56,724
Momoko-sensei warmly welcomed me⟩

22
00:00:56,791 --> 00:00:58,726
⟨At times like that...⟩

23
00:00:58,793 --> 00:01:00,795
(Mika) It's over for today.

24
00:01:03,230 --> 00:01:06,667
(Eri) I am →

25
00:01:06,734 --> 00:01:09,670
Kim Min Seok →

26
00:01:09,737 --> 00:01:11,739
I'm my fiancé.

27
00:01:15,242 --> 00:01:17,678
You look fine.

28
00:01:17,745 --> 00:01:20,181
(Minseok) Why?

29
00:01:20,247 --> 00:01:23,684
>> Do you need a reason to come see your fiance?

30
00:01:23,751 --> 00:01:26,187
(Mika) It's crazy, the heir of a conglomerate has a beautiful fiancée →

31
00:01:26,253 --> 00:01:29,190
What is this? (Kazami) Please go ahead.

32
00:01:29,256 --> 00:01:31,192
(Kazami) Please come up.

33
00:01:31,258 --> 00:01:33,260
(Eri) Thank you.

34
00:01:35,763 --> 00:01:37,698
Ah... >> Please click here →

35
00:01:37,765 --> 00:01:40,768
Thank you for calling. >> We apologize for the inconvenience.

36
00:01:43,270 --> 00:01:48,209
Um... I don't know if it will suit your taste.

37
00:01:48,275 --> 00:01:50,711
(Eri) Is it okay? (Kazami) Please, please.

38
00:01:50,778 --> 00:01:52,780
(Eri) I'll eat it.

39
00:01:54,281 --> 00:01:56,217
Yes, it's delicious!

40
00:01:56,283 --> 00:01:58,219
(Kazami) Wahaha, that was good.

41
00:01:58,285 --> 00:02:01,722
This natural sweetness will melt away the fatigue of your flight.

42
00:02:01,789 --> 00:02:03,657
(Mika) Flight?

43
00:02:03,724 --> 00:02:06,727
I just arrived from Korea.

44
00:02:08,729 --> 00:02:11,165
(Eri) It's really delicious taiyaki.

45
00:02:11,232 --> 00:02:13,167
(Kazami) Please have two or three.

46
00:02:13,234 --> 00:02:14,668
yes.

47
00:02:14,735 --> 00:02:16,237
(Minseok) Inri-chan.

48
00:02:18,239 --> 00:02:20,174
I guess it's a little good.

49
00:02:20,241 --> 00:02:31,752
♪～

50
00:02:37,758 --> 00:02:42,196
(Minseok) How did you know you were here?

51
00:02:42,263 --> 00:02:45,699
>> It doesn't matter, right?

52
00:02:45,766 --> 00:02:47,768
(Minseok) No, but.

53
00:02:49,770 --> 00:02:52,206
We are already...

54
00:02:52,273 --> 00:02:55,209
>> I'll go home today, then.

55
00:02:55,276 --> 00:02:57,278
(Minseok) Wait.

56
00:03:00,281 --> 00:03:02,716
(sound of car door closing)

57
00:03:02,783 --> 00:03:06,654
(Mika) I'm sure you've seen it before.

58
00:03:06,720 --> 00:03:09,657
Ah! It's this person after all! (Kazami) Huh?

59
00:03:09,723 --> 00:03:13,661
(Mika) Eri Shinkai is an influencer and the daughter of the president of the Shinkai Group.

60
00:03:13,727 --> 00:03:16,163
(Kazami) Influenza? influenza?

61
00:03:16,230 --> 00:03:19,166
Not an influencer.

62
00:03:19,233 --> 00:03:21,669
I see, the Shinkai Group is not only in Japan →

63
00:03:21,735 --> 00:03:24,171
We are also expanding into Korea.

64
00:03:24,238 --> 00:03:26,674
(sound of door opening)

65
00:03:26,740 --> 00:03:28,676
(Mika) Ah, Minseok-san.

66
00:03:28,742 --> 00:03:31,178
Huh? What about Eri?

67
00:03:31,245 --> 00:03:33,180
(Minseok) Ah, I'm back.

68
00:03:33,247 --> 00:03:35,182
I'm sorry.

69
00:03:35,249 --> 00:03:38,185
(Mika) I see... Hey, Minseok-san.

70
00:03:38,252 --> 00:03:40,187
As expected from the heir of a conglomerate.

71
00:03:40,254 --> 00:03:43,190
I can't believe that such an amazing person is my fiancé.

72
00:03:43,257 --> 00:03:48,762
(Minseok) Ah, no, we're not fiancéed anymore.

73
00:03:51,265 --> 00:03:54,201
My engagement with her was broken off.

74
00:03:54,268 --> 00:03:56,704
(Mika) Is that so?

75
00:03:56,770 --> 00:03:58,706
(Minseok) Yes.

76
00:03:58,772 --> 00:04:02,776
>>But why did you break off the engagement?

77
00:04:05,713 --> 00:04:07,715
(Minseok) That's...

78
00:04:12,219 --> 00:04:14,655
>>Ha! (Mika) Huh?

79
00:04:14,722 --> 00:04:18,158
(Kazami) I'm already old, so I'm feeling sleepy.

80
00:04:18,225 --> 00:04:20,160
Hey, it's only 6 o'clock.

81
00:04:20,227 --> 00:04:23,163
No, that's all for today.

82
00:04:23,230 --> 00:04:25,666
Thank you for your hard work.

83
00:04:25,733 --> 00:04:28,168
Now let's disband!

84
00:04:28,235 --> 00:04:30,170
Hey, Director.

85
00:04:30,237 --> 00:04:31,672
(Kazami) Minseok-kun.

86
00:04:31,739 --> 00:04:35,175
It's time for today to rest. You're tired.

87
00:04:35,242 --> 00:04:38,178
(Minseok) Oh no... (Kazami) I'm tired.

88
00:04:38,245 --> 00:04:41,181
If we were here, Minseok-kun wouldn't be able to rest.

89
00:04:41,248 --> 00:04:44,685
Hey, look, Momo-chan, let's go.

90
00:04:44,752 --> 00:04:46,253
(Momoko) Thank you.

91
00:04:54,261 --> 00:04:56,196
(Mika) Hey, Director.

92
00:04:56,263 --> 00:04:59,199
Good night, see you tomorrow.

93
00:04:59,266 --> 00:05:01,268
(Momoko) Good night. >> Yeah.

94
00:05:03,704 --> 00:05:06,640
I wanted to ask you a lot of things.

95
00:05:06,707 --> 00:05:08,642
(Momoko) Let's go home, Mika-chan.

96
00:05:08,709 --> 00:05:10,210
>> Yes.

97
00:05:12,212 --> 00:05:15,649
It seems like there are various reasons for this.

98
00:05:15,716 --> 00:05:18,152
But those two are so...

99
00:05:18,218 --> 00:05:19,653
(Momoko) Really?

100
00:05:19,720 --> 00:05:23,657
>>It really suited you though.

101
00:05:23,724 --> 00:05:27,161
Eri-san was beautiful.

102
00:05:27,227 --> 00:06:02,262
♪～

103
00:06:11,638 --> 00:06:13,574
(Kyoko) Momoko: Why don't you take a bath first?

104
00:06:14,975 --> 00:06:16,477
(Momoko) Yes.

105
00:06:18,545 --> 00:06:20,481
>> Nowlog?

106
00:06:20,547 --> 00:06:21,982
(Momoko) Huh? >> Huh?

107
00:06:22,049 --> 00:06:24,485
(Momoko) Huh…｡ >> Huh…｡

108
00:06:24,551 --> 00:06:27,988
What happened? Were you interested in that?

109
00:06:28,055 --> 00:06:29,990
(Momoko) Um, look...

110
00:06:30,057 --> 00:06:32,493
Takuto: Takuto told me to take a look.

111
00:06:32,559 --> 00:06:34,495
>>Ah, Taku-chan.

112
00:06:34,561 --> 00:06:37,498
(Momoko) She's a doctor and always brags about being the top follower.

113
00:06:37,564 --> 00:06:39,066
Look.

114
00:06:41,068 --> 00:06:43,003
(Kyoko) Hey, I'll do it.

115
00:06:43,070 --> 00:06:46,006
(Momoko) Hey, yeah.

116
00:06:46,073 --> 00:06:49,076
Okay, I guess I'll take a bath then.

117
00:06:59,086 --> 00:08:08,956
♪～

118
00:08:09,022 --> 00:08:16,463
(footsteps)

119
00:08:16,530 --> 00:08:19,533
(Minseok) Sorry for contacting you so suddenly.

120
00:08:23,036 --> 00:08:24,471
(Momoko) No.

121
00:08:24,538 --> 00:08:29,042
(Minseok) I really wanted to talk to you today.

122
00:08:31,044 --> 00:08:35,549
I wanted to talk to Momoko-sensei.

123
00:08:43,056 --> 00:08:44,992
(Momoko) Would you like to have a drink?

124
00:08:45,058 --> 00:08:47,060
(Minseok) Ah.

125
00:08:48,562 --> 00:08:50,497
(door chime)

126
00:08:50,564 --> 00:08:52,566
Yes.

127
00:08:54,067 --> 00:08:55,569
Ah!

128
00:08:57,070 --> 00:08:59,006
Eh, Taku-chan!

129
00:08:59,072 --> 00:09:00,574
(Takuto) Long time no see!

130
00:09:02,576 --> 00:09:04,511
I'm so grateful. >> I'm so grateful.

131
00:09:06,513 --> 00:09:09,950
Hmm. (Takuto) Hmm.

132
00:09:10,017 --> 00:09:12,953
>> Wow, it's so luxurious.

133
00:09:13,020 --> 00:09:15,455
Or rather, was it a good thing that I got it?

134
00:09:15,522 --> 00:09:18,458
(Takuto) Please, please, this is the kind of guy I got from working in the media →

135
00:09:18,525 --> 00:09:20,460
There's no point in giving it to Momoko.

136
00:09:20,527 --> 00:09:22,963
>> Eh, why? (Takuto) Because he is →

137
00:09:23,030 --> 00:09:24,965
It's definitely more dango than flowers.

138
00:09:25,032 --> 00:09:27,968
>> Huh…｡

139
00:09:28,035 --> 00:09:29,970
(Takuto) Or rather, what about Momoko?

140
00:09:30,037 --> 00:09:33,473
>>Ah, I just went out to do some errands.

141
00:09:33,540 --> 00:09:34,975
(Takuto) Hey.

142
00:09:35,042 --> 00:09:37,978
>> I honestly thought he was going out for drinks with Taku-chan.

143
00:09:38,045 --> 00:09:40,547
Ah, I think he'll be back soon.

144
00:09:46,553 --> 00:09:49,056
(Momoko) Huh. (Minseok) Huh.

145
00:09:50,557 --> 00:09:55,495
(Momoko) After taking a bath, I often drink beer on the balcony.

146
00:09:55,562 --> 00:09:59,566
It feels good to be blown by the wind.

147
00:10:06,573 --> 00:10:08,575
(Minseok) Um...

148
00:10:12,079 --> 00:10:15,515
(Minseok) I surprised you again →

149
00:10:15,582 --> 00:10:17,584
sorry.

150
00:10:22,089 --> 00:10:27,027
(Minseok) I have known her since childhood →

151
00:10:27,094 --> 00:10:30,097
It was a marriage decided by the parents.

152
00:10:32,099 --> 00:10:35,535
With the Shinkai Group expanding into Korea →

153
00:10:35,602 --> 00:10:39,039
If Hang Geum becomes a relative →

154
00:10:39,106 --> 00:10:43,610
It will be mutually beneficial.

155
00:10:47,614 --> 00:10:53,053
(Minseok) But that story is gone...

156
00:10:53,120 --> 00:10:56,623
My engagement with her has been cancelled.

157
00:10:58,125 --> 00:11:00,060
(Peach) Dissolution?

158
00:11:00,127 --> 00:11:01,628
(Minseok) Yes.

159
00:11:04,064 --> 00:11:06,500
(Momoko) Why?

160
00:11:06,566 --> 00:11:09,069
(Minseok) That's...

161
00:11:12,072 --> 00:11:17,511
(Minseok) Because I was suspected of embezzlement.

162
00:11:17,577 --> 00:11:20,080
(Momoko) Embezzlement?

163
00:11:21,581 --> 00:11:25,085
>> Korean

164
00:11:33,593 --> 00:11:36,596
(Minseok) This is a story I don't remember at all.

165
00:11:38,598 --> 00:11:41,535
But →

166
00:11:41,601 --> 00:11:45,539
Unable to clear the doubt →

167
00:11:45,605 --> 00:11:50,110
I was chased out of Korea and came to Japan.

168
00:11:54,614 --> 00:11:56,616
(Momoko) That's what happened.

169
00:12:00,620 --> 00:12:04,057
(Momoko) Minseok embezzled money.

170
00:12:08,562 --> 00:12:10,997
(Minseok) Her father is →

171
00:12:11,064 --> 00:12:16,002
When I found out that I was suspected of embezzlement →

172
00:12:16,069 --> 00:12:19,072
"I'm canceling the engagement," he said.

173
00:12:21,074 --> 00:12:26,580
That's what she wants too.

174
00:12:31,084 --> 00:12:35,088
(Minseok) That's why I...

175
00:12:41,595 --> 00:12:51,037
📱(vibration sound)

176
00:12:51,104 --> 00:12:54,040
(Minseok) Ah. (Momoko) Sorry.

177
00:12:54,107 --> 00:12:56,610
Yes, maybe.

178
00:12:58,111 --> 00:13:01,548
Yes, I understand.

179
00:13:01,615 --> 00:13:04,551
Yes, yes.

180
00:13:12,559 --> 00:13:14,494
(Momoko) I'm going home soon.

181
00:13:14,561 --> 00:13:16,496
My sister is worried.

182
00:13:16,563 --> 00:13:18,498
(Minseok) Ah, I'll send it.

183
00:13:18,565 --> 00:13:22,002
(Momoko) Ah, no, it's okay.

184
00:13:22,068 --> 00:13:24,504
Good night then.

185
00:13:24,571 --> 00:13:26,506
(Minseok) Please be careful.

186
00:13:26,573 --> 00:13:38,018
♪～

187
00:13:38,084 --> 00:13:41,021
(Momoko) Hey, Takuto was here.

188
00:13:41,087 --> 00:13:44,524
(Kyoko) I got an emergency call and went home right away.

189
00:13:44,591 --> 00:13:47,027
That's a great flower.

190
00:13:47,093 --> 00:13:50,530
(Momoko) Yeah, it's beautiful.

191
00:13:50,597 --> 00:13:53,533
>> Eh, what happened?

192
00:13:53,600 --> 00:13:56,536
Did something happen to Momoko, who is more dango than flower?

193
00:13:56,603 --> 00:13:58,538
(Momoko) There's nothing special.

194
00:13:58,605 --> 00:14:00,540
>> Really?

195
00:14:00,607 --> 00:14:02,609
(Momoko) It's true.

196
00:14:04,544 --> 00:14:06,479
(Kyoko) Then go to sleep. (Momoko) Yeah.

197
00:14:06,546 --> 00:14:09,049
(Kyoko) Good night. (Momoko) Good night.

198
00:14:15,055 --> 00:14:17,490
(Minseok) [I said, "I'm canceling the engagement."]

199
00:14:17,557 --> 00:14:22,062
[That's what she wants too]

200
00:14:24,564 --> 00:14:27,000
(Momoko) Then, what about Minseok?

201
00:14:27,067 --> 00:14:44,017
♪～

202
00:14:44,084 --> 00:14:46,086
(Minseok) Inri-chan.

203
00:14:50,090 --> 00:14:53,526
(Minseok) Happy 20th birthday.

204
00:14:53,593 --> 00:14:56,029
>>Thank you.

205
00:14:56,096 --> 00:14:58,598
(Minseok) You've become an adult.

206
00:15:00,100 --> 00:15:01,534
>> Is that all?

207
00:15:01,601 --> 00:15:04,471
(Minseok) Eh, ah, uh...｡

208
00:15:04,537 --> 00:15:06,973
>> Hey Minseok-san.

209
00:15:07,040 --> 00:15:10,977
I'll marry you

210
00:15:11,044 --> 00:15:12,979
(Minseok) Huh?

211
00:15:13,046 --> 00:15:15,982
>> Not right away, but when the time comes.

212
00:15:16,049 --> 00:15:18,485
(Minseok) What happened?

213
00:15:18,551 --> 00:15:23,490
She said she would never marry the person her parents had chosen for her.

214
00:15:23,556 --> 00:15:26,059
>>I noticed.

215
00:15:29,562 --> 00:15:35,001
I'm sure you'll make me shine.

216
00:15:35,068 --> 00:15:40,507
Because you are the person who can become the top of Fangum.

217
00:15:40,573 --> 00:15:44,010
(Minseok) What are you talking about?

218
00:15:44,077 --> 00:15:48,014
No one thinks like that.

219
00:15:48,081 --> 00:15:50,517
I'm not that kind of person. (Eri) No.

220
00:15:50,583 --> 00:15:55,588
You will definitely become the top of Fangum.

221
00:15:58,091 --> 00:16:00,093
My eyes are sure.

222
00:16:07,534 --> 00:16:09,969
📱(Eri's father) [I'll pretend there was no engagement with you]

223
00:16:10,036 --> 00:16:12,472
📱〔Eri wants that too〕

224
00:16:12,539 --> 00:16:15,475
📱〔I'm really glad it happened before I got married〕

225
00:16:15,542 --> 00:16:17,477
📱 [Call disconnection sound]

226
00:16:17,544 --> 00:16:28,988
♪～

227
00:16:29,055 --> 00:16:33,993
(Minseok) 《Why are you in front of me again?》

228
00:16:34,060 --> 00:16:46,573
♪～

229
00:16:50,610 --> 00:16:56,616
>> English

230
00:17:04,758 --> 00:17:07,694
(Staff) [Looks like you were humiliated in front of the manager]

231
00:17:07,761 --> 00:17:11,264
(Staff) [Just because he's the heir of a family, what's the point?]

232
00:17:12,766 --> 00:17:14,701
(Staff) [Thank you for your hard work] (Staff) [Thank you for your hard work]

233
00:17:14,768 --> 00:17:16,770
(Staff) [Thank you for your hard work]

234
00:17:17,303 --> 00:17:23,309
English

235
00:17:27,814 --> 00:17:30,250
(Natsume) Hanu... Huh...｡

236
00:17:30,316 --> 00:17:31,751
(Momoko) [Minseok-san →

237
00:17:31,818 --> 00:17:35,188
He is a kind person who naturally extends his helping hand to those in need.]

238
00:17:35,255 --> 00:17:38,691
[That's why everyone loves Minseok]

239
00:17:38,758 --> 00:17:41,261
(Natsume) Sorry….

240
00:17:43,263 --> 00:17:45,698
(Minseok) Um...

241
00:17:45,765 --> 00:17:48,201
Is there anything I can do?

242
00:17:48,268 --> 00:17:51,771
(Natsume) Ah, um...｡

243
00:17:53,773 --> 00:17:56,209
That customer here→

244
00:17:56,276 --> 00:18:01,714
He said he would like to send a gift called Hanu to celebrate the opening of a Korean restaurant to his Korean friend.

245
00:18:01,781 --> 00:18:05,285
English

246
00:18:18,298 --> 00:18:19,732
(Male) Please.

247
00:18:19,799 --> 00:18:21,734
(Minseok) Can I borrow it?

248
00:18:21,801 --> 00:18:23,303
>> Yes.

249
00:18:38,818 --> 00:18:41,254
(Minseok) A beckoning cat.

250
00:18:41,321 --> 00:18:43,823
>> Manekineko?

251
00:18:58,838 --> 00:19:01,841
english conversation

252
00:19:06,846 --> 00:19:09,282
(Minseok) Then this is it for me.

253
00:19:09,349 --> 00:19:12,285
>> That.

254
00:19:12,352 --> 00:19:16,289
Suggestions for gifts that combine Japanese and Korean culture→

255
00:19:16,356 --> 00:19:18,791
As a deputy manager.

256
00:19:18,858 --> 00:19:20,793
It's very educational.

257
